    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>carrot discs </strong>and <strong>onion wedges </strong>to the dish with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong>,<strong> sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>miso paste </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up then add 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[680ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil, then cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
